I have a form for requests now; check it out if you want to request a character.

Team Aqua Grunt from Pokemon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire. Trained on NAI. Tested at 0.8-1.0 strength.

A request from the form. Check out my Discord if you want to chat about video games (or yell at me about requests.)

items.name: Warhammer 40k Bionic Eye
items.description:
Cybernetic eyes really aren't something any base models I've tried have been able to do. This gives you the ability to stick them on. Currently it has a pronounced swing towards a grimdark 40k style. Not so much an issue with 40k, but I may experiment with eliminating some of that for a future version.

Example images are most un-inpainted, with a few having a few minutes of extra work to show off what you can do if you go the extra mile. Any workflow not in the generation parameters is noted in a comment on the image.

Suggested Weight: 0.7-0.9

(different models are more resistant to the concept. If I go any higher than 0.7 with my model images start getting all John Blanche style stylized and contortion of faces. Brixel Core easily tolerates 0.8 without complaint, and needs it to really pick up the eyes.)

Main keyword is: bionic eye

Useful helper words: cyborg, cable, wires

Useful negatives: grainy

The LoRA is entirely capable of getting crisp eyes with a bit of inpainting, or if you get lucky with highresfix. I get the best results inpainting the eye at high resolution and lowish denoise, with enough padding to get the other eye in frame.

items.name: Millennium Girls
items.description:
All girls were 18 or older at the time they were models!!

A long, long, long... long, time ago. People used their phone landline (that's a phone that had to be plugged into the wall for you youngsters) in order to connect to the internet. Your computer would basically make a call, there would be beeps, static, hissing. Your computer would sound like it was screeching at you, and only then could you surf the interwebs. It was really slow, so slow that "HiRes" was a 640x480 video and you would have to actually download it to view it. Then you would find out that you waited 30 minutes to see a 10 second clip that by today's standards was more like an animated GIF. Then you would realize that you got much more satisfaction from images. On a good day when the phone lines were clear you could actually view a whole set of images (about 15-20) in just a few minutes.

That's where these girls come into the "picture". Back in the late 90's and early 2000's these 8 girls were a few of the most popular teens on the internet. There were no cam sites, and no home run membership sites. Just a bunch of small studios trying to jump into the new Millennium by paying college tuition for pretty girls.

The Girls and their tags

Nicole - Nicole Scott, aka Red Hot Lauren

Ariel - Ariel Rebel

Ivana - Ivana Fukalot

KittyJ - Kitty Jung (had to add the J to avoid cat ears all the time)

April - Little April

Melissa - Melissa Ashley aka Anne Howe

Fransizka - Franziska Facella

Tawnee - Tawnee Stone

points of interest

-All girls were of legal age at the time of posing despite what their body type might imply. (I.E. KittyJ and Melissa)

-All dataset images were cropped at a 3:4 ratio. About 1/3 of the images I used to train this LoRA were already in this format, and it is also what I use most of the time. Likely will not matter when rendering but I'm just throwing that out there.

-Each girl was trained on 32 images each. All images were pulled from the same site and still easily accessible to the public.

-The LoRA is named Rev2Final because I almost had it ready to release but tried something new before I uploaded it. The end result turned out just a little better and I had thought about releasing both to allow for options but after some testing Rev2 is more capable.

-Final does not mean that I am not considering updating it. I'm actually in the process now of adding 8 images to each girl focused solely on facial features. I am also thinking of making it an even 10 since I remembered another from that time that I missed.

-Not all girls turned out to be as good as I hoped for. April for example never seems to be quite right and although Tawnee is close enough to be recognizable, she is not good enough for me. Luckily Nicole turned out mostly good or I would not be uploading it yet.

error in training found It would seem that I forgot to include April's training images so I have removed that trigger from the list, 7/8 ain't bad right?

V1.0 through V10 were a learning experience, ignore them.

V2.0 - so I learned a few things. Not all girls work at full accuracy, yet, but I'd say they're all 90% correct with a couple getting 95% or more accuracy.

Girls like Ariel and Kitty work very well but April and Dayanna are 2 of the more problematic girls. modelVersions.name: Supplemental
modelVersions.description:
This is not actually a new version of the Millennium Girls LoRA. This is a test LoRA that has 5 girls similar to the existing 10. I wanted to test a theory that a LoRA could be trained on far less images if they were similar enough to each other, yet still different enough to form a dataset. This "version" was trained on only 50 images, 10 for each girl. The smaller dataset means I was able to custom caption the images. The fact that the images were similar (same set) means that most of the caption files were or were nearly identical to each other. Choosing to add only 5 girls means that it was easier to avoid similar captioning between girls.

Remember This is not a new version but a supplemental LoRA, you will need to download Redux to have all girls.

modelVersions.name: Redux
modelVersions.description: The Millennium Girls have had almost a complete overhaul. Little April is back in the picture. (no really, I double checked) And they have been joined by two more girls from that same era, Patty Cake and Dayanna. The triggers have also changed to avoid any unwanted crossover from checkpoints and other LoRA's etc. Except for Dayanna because I could not find other aliases.

Recommended tags, sorted by outfit, with positive prompt, negative prompt, and notes:

  • No outfit/custom outfit

    • saavtuber, yellow_eyes, :3, fangs,

    • red_hair, (head_out_of_frame:1.2), english_text, claws,

    • Consider putting 'cat tail, cat ears' or her outfit tags in negatives if they conflict with your desired outfit, or 'black hair' in positives if she keeps getting different hair

  • Native outfit

    • saavtuber, nativeoutfit, yellow_eyes, :3, fangs, hair_flower, hair_ornament, red_dress, thighhighs, floral_print, bridal_gauntlets, red_shirt, off_shoulder,

    • red_hair, (head_out_of_frame:1.2), english_text, claws, playboy bunny,

    • This outfit also contains the dress, leotard, leggings in the form of 'nativeleggings', and many accessories. Get creative with your positive & negative prompts

  • Luxur outfit

    • saavtuber, luxuroutfit, yellow_eyes, :3, fangs, cropped_hoodie, crop_top, white_shirt, gym_shorts, messy_hair, hair_bun,

    • red_hair, (head_out_of_frame:1.2), english_text, claws, hair_flower, hair_ornament,

    • Goes skinnier than the other outfits for some reason. Consider 'wide hips, thick thighs'

  • Panthera outfit

    • saavtuber, pantheraoutfit, yellow_eyes, :3, fangs, hair_flower, hair_ornament, highleg_panties, cat_tail, cat_ears, animal_hands, animal_collar, jingle_bell,

    • red_hair, (head_out_of_frame:1.2), english_text, claws, (dress, shorts:1.2), long_hair, playboy_bunny, leotard,

    • Animal hands really limits what her hands can do. Consider omitting them or even putting them in negative if you want her to do something with her hands

  • Purple robe outfit

    • saavtuber, purplerobeoutfit, yellow_eyes, :3, fangs, yellow_shorts, yellow_bra, oni_horns, pubic_tattoo, floral_print, leg_tattoo, elbow_gloves, heart_ahoge,

    • red_hair, (head_out_of_frame:1.2), english_text, claws, hair_flower, hair_ornament,

    • Actually has a very difficult time making her purple robe. Does the rest of the outfit just fine, though. There weren't many instances of her using the robe to train on.

  • Shahi outfit

    • saavtuber, yellow_eyes, :3, fangs, shahioutfit, cleavage,

    • red_hair, (head_out_of_frame:1.2), english_text, claws, hair_flower, hair_ornament,

    • Very poorly trained. Not many good pics to go off of. To get light shahi, include 'white' in the prompt. For dark, 'black'. Do NOT include 'leggings' or 'legwear', ruins the outfit. Emphasizing 'shahioutfit' makes it work a little better but kills backgrounds.

Her snake tail is also tagged as 'snake_tail' in case you want to get rid of it or force it in. If you want to be accurate to her model, it only goes on native, purple robe, and gorgon. Panthera and shahi have 'cat_tail', and luxur has no tail at all.

After 96 models, 388 hours of processing, 2100 likes and 15K downloads, I want to sincerely thank the 5 people in total who supported me and allowed me to credit my colab. You made all this possible and more is coming.

The Wild Wild West is an American Western, espionage, and science fiction television series that ran on the CBS television network for four seasons from September 17, 1965, to April 11, 1969. Two satirical comedy television film sequels were made with the original cast in 1979 and 1980 and the series was adapted for a theatrical film in 1999.

Developed at a time when the television Western was losing ground to the spy genre, this show was conceived by its creator, Michael Garrison, as "James Bond on horseback." Set during the administration of President Ulysses Grant (1869â€“1877), the series followed Secret Service agents James West (Robert Conrad) and Artemus Gordon (Ross Martin) as they solved crimes, protected the President, and foiled the plans of megalomaniacal villains to take over part or all of the United States. The show featured a number of fantasy elements, such as the technologically advanced devices used by the agents and their adversaries. The combination of the Victorian era time-frame and the use of Vernean technology has led several steampunk web sites to cite the show as a pioneering influence on the genre. This aspect was accentuated even more in the 1999 film adaptation.

Despite high ratings, the series was cancelled near the end of its fourth season as a concession to Congress over television violence.

"FoodPorn is your passport to a world where words morph into pictures of irresistible, exaggerated food indulgence" -ChatGPT

This Lora was trained to produce pictures of the most over-the-top delicious foods. It should work for food generally, but will respond best to foods it was trained on. Here are some statistics about the labels that appeared in its training set, along with their frequencies:

foodporn": 124, "savory": 92, "meat": 62, "cheese": 50, "dessert": 33, "pasta": 33, "fruit": 19, "chocolate": 19, "mexican": 17, "asian": 18, "cream": 18, "vegetables": 18, "american": 16, "potato": 15, "pastry": 12, "bread": 12, "hamburger": 11, "egg": 11, "shrimp": 10, "fried": 9, "dumpling": 8, "taco": 7, "waffle": 6, "wrap": 6, "italian": 5, "quesadilla": 3, "rice": 3.

So the easiest way to prompt this lora is to just make a comma-separated list of the items you want. For example, "foodporn, savory, hamburger, pasta, potato, fried <lora:FoodPorn_v2_:1>" could be a prompt.

While this Lora was trained on the SD 1.5 base model, I strongly recommend using it with the model rMadArt , which was used for most of the images here. items.name: Alita from "Alita: Battle Angel" (2019)
items.description:
After 99 models, 400 hours of processing, 2100 likes and 15K downloads, I want to sincerely thank the 5 people in total who supported me and allowed me to credit my colab. You made all this possible and more is coming.

Alita: Battle Angel is a 2019 American cyberpunk action film based on Yukito Kishiro's manga series Gunnm (or Battle Angel Alita in English). It was directed by Robert Rodriguez, produced by James Cameron and Jon Landau, and written by Cameron and Laeta Kalogridis. Rosa Salazar stars through motion-capture animation as Alita, a cyborg who awakens in a new body without memory of her past and sets out to uncover her destiny. Christoph Waltz, Jennifer Connelly, Mahershala Ali, Ed Skrein, Jackie Earle Haley and Keean Johnson star in supporting roles.

This model is trained with SFW sources only. If you get NSFW content, you did it in purpose, didn't you?

Please provide constructive criticism.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

Prompt : Alita, big eyes, photography, trending on artstation, sharp focus, studio photo, intricate details, highly detailed, by greg rutkowski <lora:Alita:0.6>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 70, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 7, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x768, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration is optional, may provide better result if not activated.

Use Alita, big eyes as trigger.

Important:

This Lora model is a virtual representation of a natural person and it is important to emphasize that its use must not be illegal or degrading. I want to remind you that any infringement in this regard is the responsibility of the user and not that of the designer of this model.

It is crucial to respect laws and ethical standards regarding the use of this technology. Any abusive or illegal use of this model is strictly prohibited and could result in legal consequences for the user.

As the designer of this model, I take the responsibility of ensuring that it is used in an ethical and responsible manner very seriously. I rely on each user to do the same and to act in compliance with the laws and ethical standards in force.
